<br><h2 class=3D"title_grn">Definition: Ounce</h2>
<p>Note that this is a fluid ounce measuring volume, not the typical ounce =
that measures weight. It only applies for a liquid ounce in U.S. measuremen=
ts.</p>

<br><h2 class=3D"title_grn">Definition: Millilitre</h2>
<p>The millilitre (ml or mL, also spelled milliliter) is a metric unit of v=
olume that is equal to one thousandth of a litre. It is a non-SI unit accep=
ted for use with the International Systems of Units (SI). It is exactly equ=
ivalent to 1 cubic centimetre (cm=C2=B3, or, non-standard, cc).</p>


